Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 1 -- 6.50 Mills - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of LaSalle, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy a six and fifty hundredths (6.50) mills tax on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $487,500 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2025, for the purpose of capital construction and/or equipment and operating and maintaining the Parish Library and its branches?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 2 -- 2.21 Mills - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of LaSalle, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy a special tax of two and twenty-one hundredths (2.21) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $165,750 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2025, for the purpose of capital construction and/or equipment and supporting, operating and maintaining the Parish Library and its branches?
